The coronavirus pandemic has brought a time of uncertainty, tragedy and new ways of living for South Africans. Many have lost loved ones, grappled with the virus  and dealt with the ravaging effects of lockdown. SA has made many discoveries about the virus since it first hit our shores. As the country reflects on a year with Covid-19, here are some sobering and not-so-sombre facts on the pandemic in SA: While it's been a sobering year grappling with the virus, there have been some light moments to emerge from the pandemic. The most notable  came from the national lockdown, which sparked court cases, memes, new booze brews and hit songs inspired by the government's more bizarre rules. Here are a few notable ones: